# Davidson Hub (student link hub PWA)

## Stack

- **Next.js** App Router + TypeScript + **Tailwind CSS**. Upgrade packages intentionally; keep a **lockfile** committed.
- **PWA:** **Serwist only** — do not use legacy `next-pwa`. This repo uses **`@serwist/turbopack`** + **`next.config.mjs`** + **`app/sw.ts`** + **`app/serwist/[path]/route.ts`** because Next 16 builds with Turbopack; follow the **installed** Serwist Turbopack docs. (`@serwist/next` is for webpack-based builds.)
- **Icons:** Prefer **`lucide-react`** (tree-shaking, large set, good DX). **`@heroicons/react`** is fine when an icon fits better; pick one per screen/section for consistency.
- **Deploy:** Vercel (normal Node build, not static export unless explicitly required).

## Make it useful and easy (mobile-first)

- **Tap targets:** Large pill links; keep the main hub to **one short scroll** for ~5–7 links.
- **Labels:** Short, scannable titles; optional tiny subtitle where it helps (dining, maps, etc.).
- **External links:** Default `target="_blank"` and `rel="noopener noreferrer"`; use same-tab only when SSO or college flows would break in a new tab.
- **Safe areas:** Banner and bottom UI respect **`env(safe-area-inset-bottom)`** (and horizontal insets if full-bleed) on notched iPhones.
- **a11y:** Semantic structure, visible focus states, **`aria-label`** on icon-only buttons (e.g. close on the iOS banner).

## Claymorphism

- Page: soft warm off-white / light pastel (`stone-50`, `slate-50`, or similar).
- Controls: thick **pill** shapes (`rounded-2xl` / `rounded-3xl`), **bold** link text.
- **Shadows:** Define **one or two** custom `boxShadow` values in **Tailwind theme** (outer soft drop + inner light TL + inner dark BR). **Do not** paste duplicate long `shadow-[…]` strings on every component.

## PWA surface

- **`public/manifest.json`:** `display: "standalone"`, `theme_color`, `background_color`, icons **192** and **512** (placeholders OK); add **maskable** when real art exists.
- **`app/layout.tsx`:** Link manifest; `metadata` / viewport **`themeColor`** as appropriate; Apple web app meta for iOS home-screen behavior.

## Data

- **v1:** Static link list in **`app/page.tsx`** or **`lib/links.ts`** (id, label, href, optional icon name, optional category). No CMS unless asked.

## `components/IOSInstallPrompt.tsx` (client only)

- **`"use client"`**; bail if **`typeof window === 'undefined'`**.
- **Show only on iOS** (UA includes iPhone / iPad / iPod, or project-approved equivalent check).
- **Hide if already “installed” / standalone:**  
  **`window.matchMedia('(display-mode: standalone)').matches`**  
  **OR** **`(window.navigator as Navigator & { standalone?: boolean }).standalone === true`** (covers older Safari home-screen quirks).
- **Hide if dismissed:** **`localStorage.getItem('hasSeenIOSPrompt')`**; close button sets **`localStorage.setItem('hasSeenIOSPrompt', 'true')`**.
- **UI:** Sticky bottom banner, high z-index (e.g. 50), clay styling; copy: Share → Add to Home Screen.

## Scope

- Match existing project patterns; avoid drive-by refactors. One focused change beats a wide cleanup.
